%% RFID Tracking System — Granular Architecture (Mermaid)
%% Source file. Render via docs/architecture.html (open in browser, print to PDF).

%% ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
%% Diagram 1: Startup / boot sequence
%% ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U  as User (CLI)
    participant LP as listener.py
    participant DT as DwellTracker
    participant DB as SQLite (rfid_reads.db)
    participant SW as Sweeper Thread
    participant FL as Flask App

    U  ->>  LP: python listener.py
    LP ->>  DT: DwellTracker()
    DT ->>  DB: connect (WAL mode)
    DT ->>  DB: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS tag_reads
    DT ->>  DB: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS component_sessions
    DT ->>  DT: _ensure_columns()
    Note over DT,DB: Idempotent migration:<br/>add target columns,<br/>copy from any legacy column,<br/>drop legacy columns.
    DT ->>  DB: ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN first_enter_at_ant1 ...
    DT ->>  DB: UPDATE component_sessions SET <new> = <old>
    DT ->>  DB: ALTER TABLE DROP COLUMN <legacy>
    DT ->>  DT: _recover_open_sessions()
    DT ->>  DB: SELECT WHERE status IN (IN_PROGRESS, EXIT_ONLY)
    DB -->> DT: open rows
    DT ->>  DT: rebuild self._open dict (in-memory)
    DT ->>  SW: start daemon thread (_sweep_loop)
    LP ->>  FL: Flask(__name__)
    LP ->>  FL: register /tags POST
    LP ->>  FL: register /healthz GET
    LP ->>  FL: app.run(0.0.0.0:5000)
    Note over LP,FL: Listener ready.
